===Etymology===
Ancient Greek [[Μαραθών]], ''Marathōn'', a town northeast of Athens.  [[w:Phidippides_(Marathon_runner)|Phidippides]] the Greek ran the distance from Marathon to Athens to deliver a message regarding the [[w:Battle of Marathon|Battle of Marathon]].  The modern sport of marathon running is based on a run approximately the same distance.

